Package vaccine_service

package vaccine_service
  • Class
    Description
    Appointment
    Represents a vaccine appointment with three fields: a patient object, timeslot object, and a location.
    Date
    Represents a calender date with three fields: day, month, and year.
    Kiosk
    A user interface class to process the transactions entered through the console and outputs the results to the console.
    Location
    Represents locations where vaccine services are being offered.
    Patient
    Represents a Patient with three fields: the patient's first name, last name, and date of birth
    RunProject1
    This class calls the Kiosk class and starts running the vaccine clinic service.
    Schedule
    Represents schedule of vaccine appointments in 5 different counties from 9:15 to 16:45 using an array of objects.
    Time
    Represents time with two fields: hour and minute.
    Timeslot
    Represents a timeslot for vaccine appointment.
